Madison Hash House Harriers

Drinking Club with a Running Problem

Paavo

Hurley & Minocqua, WI

August 7-9, 2015

Friday, August 7

  1. Packet Pick-up: Race Packet pick-up is at the local High School. Packets can be picked up until 7pm on Friday night or from 6-630am on Saturday before the run. Last year was a complete debacle so pick up packets BEFORE the bar crawl as drunk hashers are, surprisingly, not very responsible! (who knew!) Contact Will-Ho in advance if you are unable to meet the Friday pick-up time.
  2. Dinner:  Meet some of the hashers at the Liberty Bell Chalet for a pre-race pasta dinner. A good meeting point to exchange race packets before the bar crawl. Liberty Bell Chelat Italian Restaurant
  3. Bar crawl!  Join the MH3 for a night of debauchery down Silver Street in Hurley, WI – a bar/strip club crawl down Northern WI’s street of broken dreams.  Shenanigans start around 8pm or so.  Details to follow that Friday…in true Hash fashion.
  4. Lodging: Indian Head Hotel across the river in Ironwood, MI
    1. For a bed in the “Big House”, contact Coco!  Sleeps 10+ for a cheap price.
    2. There are other options in the area so search to your own heart’s desire.

Saturday, August 8

  1. Paavo Nurmi Marathon!  For details:Paavo Race Website
  2. Sign up for either the Marathon-single (suckers), Half-Marathon-double (1 or 2 suckers), or a Marathon Relay (5 male/female hungover hashers).  Contact Will-Ho for teams.
  3. Spectators – sleep in and join the fun on Silver Street with a bloody or two.
  4. After party in Minocqua!  A hash-tastic evening at the lake at CSI’s house.

Saturday – Sunday: Minocqua Details (from Hurley):

12771 Duner Point Ln, Minocqua

Directions

  • South on Hwy 51 towards Minocqua
  • Right on Hwy 70 West ~ 5miles
  • Right on Shishebogama Dr (a wooden church on the right; Black Bear Bar/Grill is ahead on the left)o Follow this through the stop sign to the end of the road, ~1.5miles
  • Left onto Florsheim Rd for ~0.5 miles
  • Left onto Duner Pt Ln (road sign behind the trees, first paved road and not driveway – easy to miss!!!!!)
  • We are 5th drive on the left – address on the post, probably marked with flour

Details

  1. Hash cash = $20 for Saturday lodging, beer, dinner and Sunday breakfast. Whiners pay an extra $5.
  2. Parking in the driveway – should fit everyone’s car, but I encourage carpooling. If your car doesn’t fit, there’s no place else to park but the ditch.
  3. Beds available for ~20 people!!!! Preference goes to Paavo runners. Contact CSI. Bring a sleeping bag to sleep on…I’m not washing your dirty-ass sheets all Sunday!
  4. Room for camping!!!  Chunk of property on a slope – beware of sleep-rolling down the hill.
  5. House is on the lake! We can go tubing around the lake, there may be a trampoline hooked up, and we have a few kayaks & paddle boards – or bring your own. Fishing is also good.
  6. No pets – leave them at home.
  7. Mass drinking to remain outdoors unless weather doesn’t cooperate – in which case, Minocqua bars will be (unknowingly) open to the hash.
  8. If you want other drinks or snacks, you’ll pass a Trigg’s grocery/liquor store on Hwy 70 West
